One person has been shot and wounded by bandits during a Saturday morning raid at Mogil village in Kerio Valley.The bandits have staged three more attacks in the area in two days after Deputy President William Ruto attended a peace rally in the region.Elgeyo Marakwet police chief Sharrif Abdallah said the victim was shot on the head and had been taken to Eldoret for treatment. Elders have started a process to reconcile communities in the region.[VIDEO] State ready to end cattle rustling, DP Ruto assures Kerio Valley residents"Our leaders must sit and agree on this issue of security because it is leading to the loss of lives of our people, we must have a conclusion to this and the sooner the better," he stated.